QuickCompare() - Method in class mainForm
This method is used for statistically comparing Array size against sorting time, it creates an array of quickSort objects, an array of threads to run each sorting algorithm and an ArrayList to hold the data.
quickS - Variable in class drawPanel
 
QuickSort() - Method in class mainForm
This method creates a quickSort with 275 values in its array for animation purposes, the drawPanel class is passed in but no Array List as the data is not required for analysis.
quickSort - Class in <Unnamed>
The quickSort class is is used to implement a Quick Sorting process on an Array of random integers that are automatically generated by the algorithm, the class can be used to either animate the bubble sort process or record the time taken to fully sort a single array.

Constructor for quickSort
QuickSort(int[], int, int) - Method in class quickSort
QuickSort method, calls partition method that returns the middle index for the array then recursively calls itself to perform a QuickSort on the left portion of the array and the right portion until the array is reduced to one item
